 it did not begin with nothing.

117
00:07:19,780 --> 00:07:23,500
 So it's not really creation out of nothing in Genesis one.

118
00:07:23,500 --> 00:07:26,780
 It begins with water and chaos.

119
00:07:26,780 --> 00:07:30,700
 (speaking in foreign language)

120
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:36,700
 And again, it's not talking about natural sciences.

121
00:07:36,700 --> 00:07:38,260
 It's talking about theology.

122
00:07:38,260 --> 00:07:40,580
 It talks about God taking control

123
00:07:40,580 --> 00:07:43,780
 using familiar concepts to the ancient people.

124
00:07:43,780 --> 00:07:46,940
 And he, God himself, the only creator,

125
00:07:46,940 --> 00:07:49,260
 he divide the waters and hold them back.

126
00:07:49,260 --> 00:07:51,820
 And that shows the power of God.

127
00:07:51,820 --> 00:07:55,740
 (speaking in foreign language)

128
00:07:55,740 --> 00:08:01,900
 So the same thing here in the psalm,

129
00:08:01,900 --> 00:08:05,060
 in the first three verses,

130
00:08:05,060 --> 00:08:07,180
 the writer is trying to use the same language

131
00:08:07,180 --> 00:08:11,340
 and same idea to tell us to declare the power of God.

132
00:08:11,340 --> 00:08:15,260
 (speaking in foreign language)

133
00:08:15,260 --> 00:08:18,180
 And then second point here is that

134
00:08:18,180 --> 00:08:19,980
 the psalm is trying to tell you

135
00:08:19,980 --> 00:08:22,380
 that you have to focus on the presence,

136
00:08:22,380 --> 00:08:23,900
 the dwelling of God.

